name: polyurethane production, flexible foam, MDI-based | polyurethane, flexible foam | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/24669/documentation

This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of one possible composition of polyurethane (PUR) flexible foam (density 45 to 53 kg/m³). Flexible polyurethane foam is used to manufacture mattresses, upholstered furniture and car seats, but also acoustic insulation boards, carpet underlays, household sponges, clothing and sportswear, packaging and many other applications. The MDI-based foams are increasingly used for bedding applications due to their viscoelastic properties (also known as “memory” and pressure-relieving properties. The inventory is estimated based on industrial data.;References:;Adam, N., Avar, G., Blankenheim, H., Friederichs, W., Giersig, M., Weigand, E., Halfmann, M., Wittbecker, F.-W., Larimer, D.-R., Maier, U., Meyer-Ahrens, S., Noble, K.-L. and Wussow, H.-G. 2005. Polyurethanes. Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry.;[This dataset is meant to replace the following datasets:; - polyurethane production, flexible foam, GLO, 1997 - 2020 (59a2166d-0a7c-5662-8ba2-29c2c19f573b)]

From reception of raw materials at the factory gate.

This activity ends with the production of 1 kg of PUR flexible foam.
category: C:Manufacturing/20:Manufacture of chemicals and chemical products/201:Manufacture of basic chemicals, fertilizers and nitrogen compounds, plastics/2013:Manufacture of plastics and synthetic rubber in primary forms

processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Polyurethane is made by reacting diisocyanates and polyols. To generate PU foam, addition of water to the main reagents causes a side reaction producing carbon dioxide, which acts as a blowing agent. Flexible slabstock polyurethane foams are produced as large blocks using a continuous process with minimal human handling. Continuous foam machines are the standard in Europe today.;The process represents production with water as a blowing agent, althought this might not be the case all over the world. If this is important in your study, make sure to check which blowing agent is used and replace it, if necessary.;References:;The full report can be accessed here: https://www.europur.org/images/20150821_EPD_EUROPUR_PU_foam.pdf (last accessed 2020-12-14).;The data is a copy of the corresponding RER dataset, uncertianty has been adjusted accrodingly.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: The dataset is a copy of the corresponding RER dataset, uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Data based on industry report and expert judgement.

exchanges.description: PUR flexible foam is used for manufacturing products such as mattresses, cushions and car seats.
